                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811.5124/19.]</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Minister of Denmark</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Denmark</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-10-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 24, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary of State</hi>: Referring to the memorandum of
                    the Department of State addressed to this Legation on February 7th, 1912, with
                    regard to the interpretation of Article 7 of the Treaty between Denmark and the
                    United States of April 26th, 1826, I beg to state that the question of the rate
                    of the inheritance tax on the estate of the late Ane Margrethe Andersen having
                    been decided against the heirs in the District Court of Iowa, the case will be
                    appealed, on behalf of the said heirs, to the Supreme Court of the State of
                    Iowa.</p>
                <p>I am directed by my Government to ascertain whether, in case the decision of the
                    Supreme Court of Iowa should also go against the heirs, an appeal to the Supreme
                    Court of the United States would be possible, and I should feel greatly obliged
                    to your excellency for submitting this question to the competent official and
                    informing me of his reply.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.].</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">C. Brun.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
